external_knowledge:
- "pioneers in their journey" refers to users who have performed their first activity;
- "unlocked the door to the digital world" refers to the first successful login attempt;
- The first activity is identified by the earliest `activity_time` after the first successful login.

- 'Successfully navigated the digital gates' refers to users who have successfully logged in;
- 'Engaged in the realms of viewing or editing' refers to users who have performed 'view' or 'edit' activities;
- 'Possess the key to the user-view chamber' refers to users who have the 'view_user' permission.

- "user_theme" refers to the preferred theme set by the user in their account settings;
- "2FA method" is the method used by the user for two-factor authentication, enhancing account security;
- "login attempts" is the number of times a user has tried to log into their account;
- "activity logs" is the number of actions recorded in the system by the user.

