- "Top three most frequent activities" means the activities with the highest occurrence counts for each user.

- 'wielding the power to manage users or reports' refers to users with 'manage_users' or 'manage_reports' permissions;
- 'maintaining an active session' refers to users with active sessions;
- 'successfully logging in within the past month' refers to users who have had a successful login attempt in the last month;
- 'securing their access with two-factor authentication' refers to users who have two-factor authentication enabled;
- 'leaving a footprint in the bustling city of New York' refers to users who have logged in from New York.

- 'digital garden' refers to the database containing user interactions;
- 'blossomed' implies that the user has either made at least one login attempt or has at least one active session;
